151
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,440
No need to go.

152
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:20,430
She was lying.

153
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,440
Why are you locking the door?

154
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:33,800
What's wrong?

155
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:45,320
What's the deal with

156
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:47,390
those two police officers who just came?

157
00:10:47,390 --> 00:10:48,130
I don't know.

158
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,670
Don't lie to me.

159
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:52,600
I'm your mother, I can tell.

160
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:01,600
Whatever is going on
between you and Su Muxin,

161
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:03,190
you need to tell me clearly.

162
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:03,970
That way,

163
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,080
I'll know

164
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,630
how to handle the situation for you

165
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:07,690
and how to help you.

166
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,630
Help?

167
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,390
Since you were a kid,

168
00:11:12,410 --> 00:11:14,510
haven't I always been the one
making decisions for you?

169
00:11:14,510 --> 00:11:15,510
When have you ever made

170
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:17,240
a correct decision on your own?

171
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,020
Tell me now.

172
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:22,720
Fine.

173
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,480
Then I'll tell you,

174
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,540
you need to help me.

175
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:30,800
Su Muxin's lover, Shi Yue

176
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:32,630
is dead.

177
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,010
The police are investigating him.

178
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,630
I can't reach him either.

179
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,040
I don't know where he's gone.

180
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,560
He probably ran away.

181
00:12:01,630 --> 00:12:02,080
Hello.

182
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:03,840
Any discoveries?

183
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:04,940
We rechecked

184
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,000
the area around

185
00:12:06,030 --> 00:12:07,510
the North Bus Terminal as you suggested.

186
00:12:07,510 --> 00:12:08,390
Outside the south gate,

187
00:12:08,390 --> 00:12:09,670
there's an abandoned construction site.

188
00:12:09,670 --> 00:12:11,240
Many people park their cars there;

189
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,390
it's basically a parking lot.

190
00:12:12,390 --> 00:12:13,000
But I checked,

191
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:13,720
and there are no surveillance cameras

192
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,910
or staff managing it.

193
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,550
There's high vehicle turnover.

194
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:17,390
Then Su Muxin probably

195
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:18,390
didn't take a bus.

196
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:19,000
Yes.

197
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,270
It seems

198
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:21,670
highly likely now.

199
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,020
We've checked all four buses,

200
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,380
and no one saw Su Muxin.

201
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:27,390
It must be Su Muxin's diversion tactic.

202
00:12:27,390 --> 00:12:28,480
He probably left

203
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,670
by car from that parking lot.

204
00:12:29,670 --> 00:12:30,470
I understand.

205
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,370
Report this to Captain Gao.

206
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:35,440
Mentor.

207
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:38,280
You think Su Muxin is still in Yunzhou?

208
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:41,630
Qu Tong disappeared

209
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,080
for two hours this afternoon.

210
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,910
She and Su Muxin are both from Yunzhou.

211
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:45,550
So,

212
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:46,600
Qu Tong returned to Yunzhou

213
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,330
specifically to meet Su Muxin?

214
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,510
It's very likely.

215
00:12:54,510 --> 00:12:56,510
that they've probably already met.

216
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:06,690
[July 18, Third day of the incident]

217
00:13:56,670 --> 00:13:57,600
Is anyone there?

218
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,250
Hello?

219
00:13:59,670 --> 00:14:00,470
Anybody home?

220
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,070
Who are you?

221
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,240
Who let you in?

222
00:14:05,390 --> 00:14:06,670
This is my daughter's place.

223
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,530
I'm her mother.

224
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,300
You're her mother?

225
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:13,120
Then you'd better clean up quickly.

226
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,320
This apartment can't be

227
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:15,200
rented out anymore,

228
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,750
nor lived in.

229
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,150
Since I rented it to your daughter,

230
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:21,550
I've had nothing but bad luck.

231
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:23,870
Wait, what do you mean?

232
00:14:23,910 --> 00:14:25,310
What do you mean by having

233
00:14:25,630 --> 00:14:27,200
bad luck renting to my daughter?

234
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,200
Your daughter was

235
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,930
someone's mistress,

236
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:30,790
seducing married men.

237
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:31,600
She did shameless things

238
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,750
in my apartment,

239
00:14:32,910 --> 00:14:33,970
do you understand?

240
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,150
Say it again.

241
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:36,030
What should I say?

242
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,240
Don't you know your own daughter?

243
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,200
Say that again!

244
00:14:38,390 --> 00:14:39,190
What's wrong?

245
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:39,670
Speak!

246
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,080
Wearing makeup to seduce men,

247
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:41,510
shameless!

248
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:43,270
What do you mean by seducing men?

249
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:44,360
This is my house!

250
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,960
You deserve it. You'll pay for this!

251
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,960
Get out of here!

252
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:47,840
This is my house!

253
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:48,750
Get out now!

254
00:15:04,790 --> 00:15:05,790
Sweetie.

255
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:43,200
I'm leaving now.

256
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:43,960
See you.

257
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:50,360
[1986]

258
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,480
Mom, you're off work.

259
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:02,880
You came to pick me up.

260
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:05,180
What are you looking at?

261
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,750
She's so beautiful.

262
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,440
How can she be so pretty?

263
00:16:12,590 --> 00:16:14,180
In my eyes,

264
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,320
you're the most beautiful.

265
00:16:18,790 --> 00:16:20,260
Let's go home.

266
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,000
Let's go home.

267
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:21,390
Go.

268
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,020
Mom, I'm home.

269
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:43,190
Welcome back.

270
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:44,070
Quickly

271
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:45,670
put down your backpack
and wash your hands.

272
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:46,150
Okay.

273
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,780
Dinner will be ready soon.

274
00:17:05,310 --> 00:17:05,780
Mom,

275
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:07,400
did you buy this for me?

276
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,369
I don't know.

277
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,060
Stop teasing me, Mom.

278
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,640
Mom, do I look pretty?

279
00:18:03,830 --> 00:18:04,590
Mrs. Shi.

